cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with sequence-to-sequence models and speech recognition, which are both subfields of natural language processing. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also likely as the paper specifically mentions experiments on speech recognition datasets. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a broad category that could apply to many papers, but it is relevant here as the paper discusses a new method for training a sequence-to-sequence model using policy gradient methods. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another broad category that could apply to many papers, but it is relevant here as the paper discusses a model that can be used for voice-based instantaneous translation, which is an application of AI. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses a method for producing outputs in an online setting, which could be seen as a control problem.
